t: Private-label war: WSJ reports Amazon to expand its store-brand offerings – Orange County Register
s: May 16, 2016 - Amazon is planning to expand the store-brand items it sells to new categories including food and household products, according to a report by The Wall Street Journal. The new products could include nuts and spices and other consumer goods such as diapers and laundry detergent.

t: Orange-winged amazon - Wikipedia
s: February 17, 2025 - The orange-winged amazon (Amazona amazonica), also known locally as orange-winged parrot and loro guaro, is a large amazon parrot. It is a resident breeding bird in tropical South America, from Colombia, Trinidad and Tobago south to Peru, Bolivia and central Brazil.
